:QUOTE
Every scene deserves a score. AI makes that possible for any filmmaker.

:INFO
AI Music Tools for Indie Film Scoring
Suno, Udio, and similar tools let indie filmmakers generate original music tracks without a composer budget. With the right workflow you can score an entire short film in a single afternoon.

:COUNTER.half
120 Seconds
Maximum generation length per track on most tools
|
:COUNTER.half
5 Variations
Generate per scene and select the best fit

:PATH
Describe Phase
Write a detailed music prompt: tempo, mood, instrumentation, scene context. The more specific you are, the better the output matches picture.

:PATH
Generate Phase
Run your prompt through Suno or Udio. Generate five variations per scene. Download the two best candidates.

:PATH
Mix Phase
Import AI tracks into your video editor or DAW. Trim to scene length. Adjust levels so music sits under dialogue without competing.

:CHECKLIST
Film Scoring Workflow Checklist
[ ] List every scene requiring music
[ ] Write a one-sentence mood description per scene
[ ] Generate five tracks per scene
[ ] Select best candidate for each scene
[ ] Export stems if available for easier mixing
[ ] Sync music to picture in editing software
[ ] Check licensing terms for distribution

:NOTE
Most AI music platforms offer royalty-free licenses for content created on their platform. Verify the terms before festival submission or commercial distribution. Save your generation prompts alongside each track file.